Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro Advances; Ledesma Retreats

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-16T17:04:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-advances-ledesma-retreats.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:47 p.m.  New York  time.  The Merval Index fell 0.5 percent to 2,757.54.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   rose 4.9 percent to 10.75 pesos,
its highest price in a week. Argentina’s largest lender by
market value will repurchase 200 million pesos ($48 million) in
shares, according to a statement posted on the website of the
Buenos Aires stock exchange.  Ledesma SA (LEDE)   fell 1.4 percent to 7.3 pesos, ending
a three-day winning streak. Argentina’s largest sugar producer
fell in line with the price of the sweetener in New York, which
tumbled the most in six months on signs that global supply will
top demand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
